{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879025031,"sessionID":"ses_2855e09b0ffeOwnQksGdceY7xM","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa36ca4001JRBEaUJTzBy55T","messageID":"msg_d7aa35f4d001BauT5x6ORsuM1C","sessionID":"ses_2855e09b0ffeOwnQksGdceY7xM","type":"text","text":"I found the issue. The `jwt.Parse` call doesn't use `jwt.WithLeeway()` to account for clock skew during the initial parsing phase. The jwt/v5 library validates `exp` and `nbf` claims during parsing, before our custom validation runs.","time":{"start":1775879025029,"end":1775879025029}}}
